                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2703</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Irkutsk</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HEL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d465fn1">Sent via the Legation in China.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Irkutsk</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 14, 1918</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.57 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>85. Referring my No. 81 [82?], 13th. <persName>Golovachev</persName> will
                    probably visit Peking and advocate the recognition of Omsk government. I <pb
                        facs="0471" n="381" xml:id="pg_381"/> have to suggest great caution in
                    dealing with this question. Such recognition would immediately estrange Samara,
                    Orenburg, and Ekaterinburg. Government [conference] now convened at Ufa in the
                    attempt to form all-Russian government. Omsk government reluctantly sent
                    delegates at late date to attend Ufa conference.</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
